{{italic title}} [[File:Winslow Homer - The Bright Side - Google Art Project.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''The Bright Side'', 1865, by [[Winslow Homer]]]] '''''The Bright Side''''' is an oil painting by the American artist [[Winslow Homer]]. Painted in 1865, the concluding year of the [[American Civil War]], the work depicts four [[African American]] [[Union Army]] [[teamster]]s sitting on the sunny side of a [[Sibley tent]].<ref name = "simpson">{{Cite book | publisher = The Fine Arts Museums of San Francisco, Bedford Arts, Publishers | isbn = 0884010600 | last = Simpson | first = Marc | title = Winslow Homer, Paintings of the Civil War | pages = 166–172 | accessdate = 2013-02-15 | url = http://www.tfaoi.com/newsm1/n1m684.htm }}</ref> The painting is in the collection of the [[Fine Arts Museums of San Francisco]]-([[De Young (museum)|De Young]])
Its dimensions are 33.7&nbsp;cm (13.27 in.) x 44.5&nbsp;cm (17.52 in.)<ref>{{Cite web | title = The Bright Side - Winslow Homer - 1865 | work = The Athenaeum | accessdate = 2013-02-16 | url = http://www.the-athenaeum.org/art/detail.php?ID=444 }}</ref>
From November 2012 to September 2013, the painting was on display at the [[Smithsonian American Art Museum]].<ref>{{Cite web | title = Wall Text, The Civil War and American Art | work = Smithsonian American Art Museum | accessdate = 2013-02-16 | date = 2012-11-14 | url = http://americanart.si.edu/search/results/?q=%22Brierwood+Pipe%22 }}</ref>
